This place is awesome!  If you’re looking for good food, good drinks, a comfortable atmosphere and a little history, this is the spot.  The better half and I planned on getting apps and burgers but settled on apps and beers as they were HUGE. The nachos are a step up from most of the bar nachos I’ve had and the potato boxty was epic. The apps are pretty filling so maybe split one with someone and leave room for entrees.  The bartender/server was really nice and even though it looked like he was the only one working, he seemed to be keeping up with the guests just fine.  The atmosphere is really nice, it’s big but feels smaller and cozy. They have TouchTunes which is nice but even when it wasn’t playing the music selection was nice.  I think my only criticism is the price of the Guinness drafts. For an Irish spot I would hope they would be a little more reasonable but all in all it’s not like it’s the most I’ve paid for it lol It’s not a big enough deal to keep this place from being 5starts by any stretch.

This is your traditional, cozy, rundown (used in the most positive way possible) and beautiful Irish pub. There is no shortage of good beer and whiskey. The food is excellent. I plan on having many more after work rounds here.  Also a fun fact. This place had a scene in Oceans 11. This is where Danny Ocean (George Clooney) recruits Linus Caldwell (Matt Damon).

Emmit’s is an Irish bar that’s full of colorful history. It’s been a hangout for the mob, judges and firefighters, and now a more homogenous group of people who just want to get a drink. In recent history, it’s served as a backdrop for movies like Uncle Buck and Backdraft. The bar itself is very open and inviting, with multiple TVs to watch sports and enjoy traditional Irish favorites like Irish stew.
Irish gem!! I had a great time here, great selection of beer. Good music and fun environment
A very sold west town irish pub with two levels.  Worth a visit if you are drinking your way through west town.
Killer Irish bar in a killer location.  Very laid back atmosphere, not as loud as many of it's neighboring watering holes.

Emmit's reminds me of this down to earth Irish pub down in Champaign UofI campus called Murphy's Pub. It's very comfortable. It has plenty of seating and fairly quiet for a bar. They have plenty of tv's and a good selection of beer.
This place is great! It has a unique feel, lots of socialization and authenticity! The building has a lot of history too!
When you are looking for a chill bar to catch up with friends, Emmit's is a great little spot to meet up. They have tables on the second floor away from the action to enjoy some drinks and talk.

This place looks beautiful and makes you want to celebrate St. Paddy's, but it is a d-bag haven. I was there on a Thursday and saw at least three people falling-over drunk (like the "do they have alcohol poisoning?" level) and my friends and I kept on getting bumped into by a group of people who I'm pretty sure just couldn't stand up straight anymore. (We were sitting in stools at the bar.) Beer selection is mediocre, drinks sound interesting but are weak. With so many other options in town, skip Emmit's and adventure elsewhere.

Being so close to the Grand blue line stop makes this a good option to grab a few drinks after work away from the craziness of the bars in River North. Food is typical bar food - nothing special. The staff here is generally pretty nice although not incredibly attentive.

unique irish bar that loads of fun! grab some friends and enjoy happy hour or watch a game. this is a chicago staple and located in an area with great restaurants. i believe a few movies have been filmed here. check it out.

Great Irish Pub, always an awesome time on St. Patty's Day. If you want an authentic Irish Pub this is a great place. I have been there several times and the beer flows and the food is good. Lots of action on the weekends and always a great after work spot.

Emmit's is a local gem. It's run by firefighters and has a very native Chicago vibe. The Guinness is delicious and the staff is very friendly. It's always packed with regulars so it's a good place to hang out and get to know people.
A place that is a fun starting point for a great night.  The staff is friendly and playful and really makes it easy to come back.

Do you like George Clooney and Matt Damon? Do you want to sit in the same booth as them in "Oceans 11"?  Well if you said yes then this is the place you need to come to. In fact, if you are a Hollywood fan, you are gonna love this place. This was the family bar in the short lived CBS drama called "Turks". And who can forget "Uncle Bucks" bar called O'Sullivans. I miss John Candy but his movie spirit lives on in here. Okay enough with the trivia. This place is an Irish bar and there is always the big game on the screen.  The food is good but it is your typical Bar food. It's not going to win Top Chef but you are going to walk away feeling satisfied.
Great Guinness but service is outstanding!!

I wandered into Emmit's while trying to kill some time before heading to a stand-up show to meet a friend. I happened upon a great Guinness beer draft pouring competition, and got sucked in. The decor is nice, and you can definitely tell that this is a firemen bar. Nonetheless, I felt welcome, and had quick service from the workers there. I had the opportunity to pour my own pint of Guinness after a quick demo by an actual brewmaster out of Dublin! I thought this was a great event, and I heard that Emmit's regularly does this sort of thing. A cozy place and a great evening.
Definitely a staple of Chicago. Great Guinness pints there.
